This article is a press briefing on the government's response to the Ebola epidemic in West Africa. The briefing includes statements from Assistant to the President for Homeland Security Lisa Monaco, Secretary of HHS Sylvia Burwell, Director of the National Institute of Infectious Diseases Dr. Anthony Fauci, USAID Administrator Dr. Raj Shah, and Commander of AFRICOM General David Rodriguez. The briefing emphasizes that the Ebola outbreak is a national security priority and that the US is taking a whole-of-government approach to control the epidemic. The US is focusing on controlling the epidemic in West Africa, enhancing domestic preparedness, and rallying the international community to contribute to the response. The briefing also highlights the importance of the US healthcare infrastructure and the efforts to develop vaccines and treatments for Ebola. The officials express confidence in the ability to contain and stop the epidemic.